13 WHEREAS, across the United States, the week of May 11 through
14 May 17, 2025, is being recognized as "National Police Week"; and
15 WHEREAS, on October 1, 1962, the United States Congress approved
16 a joint resolution authorizing the President of the United States to
17 designate May 15 of each year as "Peace Officers Memorial Day" in
18 honor of law enforcement officers who have been killed, disabled, or
19 otherwise injured in the line of duty and the calendar week during
20 which May 15 occurs as "National Police Week"; and
21 WHEREAS, by proclamation dated May 4, 1963, President John F.
22 Kennedy designated May 15, 1963, and each succeeding May 15 as
23 "Peace Officers Memorial Day" and the week of May 12 through May 18,
